Parallelisation Experiment

2023-07-20

1. Block Range

The experiment was conducted for the block range from 5,000,000 to 6,000,000. The parallelisation experiment was performed with following configuration: Geth VM and Geth MPT.

2. Degree of Parallelisation

We have 999,380 blocks of which 791,399 are parallelisable. 20.81% of blocks are strictly sequential (not parallelisable) blocks. The maximal achievable parallelism in a block is 4.017. The geometric mean of the speedup is 1.277.

3. Number of Transactions per Block

We have on average 4.7767726 transactions per block. The smallest number of transactions per block is 1 and the largest number is 148. The distribution of number of transactions per block is shown below:

4. Processor Utilisation / Efficiency

The lower bound of the processor utilisation is 55.4% on average and with a maximum of 26 processors (upper bound).

5. Sequential Block Runtime
